sec.p:
Particle concentrations varied with time depending on the corresponding changes of activities inside the classrooms. The profiles of the indoor and outdoor RSP concentration levels of the selected schools in Kuala Terengganu are shown in Figures 2 and 3, respectively. Distribution of indoor RSP concentration levels were


(a) SKBW: from 19 to 47 µg/m3;

(b) SKPP: from 6 to 27 µg/m3;

(c) SKSS1: from 9 to 44 µg/m3;

(d) SKC: from 13 to 105 µg/m3;

(e) SKGB: from 6 to 90 µg/m3;

(f) SKTAM: from 8 to 64 µg/m3 and

(g) SKKGB: from 7 to 135 µg/m3.

Fig. 2
Distribution of indoor respirable suspended particulate (RSP) matter concentrations in each school.
Fig. 3
Distribution of outdoor respirable suspended particulate (RSP) matter concentrations in each school.

Meanwhile, the profile of outdoor RSP concentration levels were


(a) SKBW: from 6 to 22 µg/m3;

(b) SKPP: from 4 to 14 µg/m3;

(c) SKSS1: from 6 to 40 µg/m3;

(d) SKC: from 8 to 78 µg/m3;

(e) SKGB: from 3 to 78 µg/m3;

(f) SKTAM: from 7 to 49 µg/m3 and

(g) SKKGB: from 6 to 74 µg/m3.
